His long, nimble fingers wouldn’t stop moving—drumming on the seat, sweeping his hairbehind his ears, fiddling with the buttons of his army fatigue jacket.
Either the kid was naturally hyper or he was hopped up on enough sugar and caffeineto give a heart attack to a water buffalo.
