“It’s worse than that.
I don’t know who I am.
Maybe that’s what it was: the NationalMuseum of Nowhere, Jason thought.
A cold wind blew across the desert.
Jason hadn’t paid much attention to what he was wearing, but it wasn’t nearlywarm enough: jeans and sneakers, a purple T-shirt, and a thin black windbreaker.
“We go to the ‘WildernessSchool’”—Leo made air quotes with his fingers.
“Which means we’re ‘bad kids.
Is it all coming back to you now?”“No.
None of them looked like hardened criminals, but hewondered what they’d all done to get sentenced to a school for delinquents, and he wondered why he belonged with them.
