“That was enough lightning to kill twenty men!”“My turn,” Jason said.
He let his instincts take over, flipping the coin in the air like he’d done it a thousand times.
Hecaught it in his palm, and suddenly he was holding a sword—a wickedly sharp double-edged weapon.
The ridged grip fit his fingers perfectly, and thewhole thing was gold—hilt, handle, and blade.
