As far as Jason couldtell, it didn’t even have a bathroom.
The walls were carved with alcoves, each holding a bronze brazier or a golden eagle statue on a marble pedestal.
Inthe center of the room, a twenty-foot-tall, full-color statue of Zeus in classic Greek robes stood with a shield at his side and a lightning bolt raised, readyto smite somebody.
Black hair? Nope.
Grumbly expression? Well, maybe.
In his robes and sandals, Zeus looked like a really buff, really angry hippie.
