“We’ll check it out on foot.
The signs said Grant Park, and Jason imagined it would’ve been a nice place in thesummer; but now it was a field of ice, snow, and salted walkways.
The dragon’s hot metal feet hissed as they touched down.
Festus flapped his wingsunhappily and shot fire into the sky, but there was no one around to notice.
The wind coming off the lake was bitter cold.
Anyone with sense would beinside.
Jason’s eyes stung so badly, he could barely see.
One of his ruby eyes flickered, so it looked like he was blinking.
